  "chapter": {
    "number": 29,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Woe to David’s City"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to you, O Ariel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2611
          },
          {
            "text": "the city of Ariel where David camped!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Year upon year",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let your festivals recur.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And I will constrain Ariel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there will be mourning and lamentation;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "she will be like an altar hearth",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2612
          },
          {
            "text": "before Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will camp in a circle around you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will besiege you with towers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and set up siege works against you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will be brought low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will speak from the ground,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and out of the dust",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your words will be muffled.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your voice will be like a spirit from the ground;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your speech will whisper out of the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But your many foes will be like fine dust,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the multitude of the ruthless like blowing chaff.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then suddenly, in an instant,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "you will be visited by the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with thunder and earthquake and loud noise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with windstorm and tempest and consuming flame of fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the many nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "going out to battle against Ariel—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even all who war against her,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "laying siege and attacking her—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will be like a dream,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a vision in the night,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "as when a hungry man dreams he is eating,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then awakens still hungry;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as when a thirsty man dreams he is drinking,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then awakens faint and parched.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So will it be for all the many nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who go to battle against Mount Zion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Stop and be astonished;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "blind yourselves and be sightless;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "be drunk, but not with wine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "stagger, but not from strong drink.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has poured out on you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a spirit of deep sleep.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has shut your eyes, O prophets;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has covered your heads, O seers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "And the entire vision will be to you like the words sealed in a scroll. If it is handed to someone to read, he will say, “I cannot, because it is sealed.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "Or if the scroll is handed to one unable to read, he will say, “I cannot read.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "Therefore the Lord said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“These people draw near to Me with their mouths",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and honor Me with their lips,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but their hearts are far from Me.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Their worship of Me is but rules taught by men.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2613
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will again confound these people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with wonder upon wonder.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The wisdom of the wise will vanish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the intelligence of the intelligent will be hidden.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2614
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who dig deep",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to hide their plans from the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In darkness they do their works and say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Who sees us, and who will know?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have turned things upside down,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as if the potter were regarded as clay.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Shall what is formed say to him who formed it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“He did not make me”?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2615
          },
          {
            "text": "Can the pottery say of the potter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“He has no understanding”?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Sanctification for the Godly"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a very short time,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will not Lebanon become an orchard,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the orchard seem like a forest?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day the deaf will hear the words of the scroll,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and out of the deep darkness the eyes of the blind will see.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The humble will increase their joy in the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the poor among men will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the ruthless will vanish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the mockers will disappear,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and all who look for evil",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be cut down—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "those who indict a man with a word,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who ensnare the mediator at the gate,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and who with false charges",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "deprive the innocent of justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "Therefore the LORD who redeemed Abraham says of the house of Jacob:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“No longer will Jacob be ashamed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no more will his face grow pale.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For when he sees his children around him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the work of My hands,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will honor My name,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will sanctify the Holy One of Jacob,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will stand in awe",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of the God of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the wayward in spirit will come to understanding,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those who grumble will accept instruction.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
